Mech Project Roadmap
===============================================================================

1. Project Status
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(1.1) Stage 1 - Alpha `v0.0.1` - `v0.0.6`

Conception: started 2014
Implementation: started 2018

(1.2) Stage 2 - Beta `v0.1.0` - `v0.4+` (???)

Started: December 2022
Currently: `v0.3.5` (Spring 2026)

- `v0.1` proof of concept `Concluded 2023`
- `v0.2` data specification    `Concluded 2025`
- `v0.3` program specification !!Started 2026!!
- `v0.4` system specification `TBD`

(1.3) Stage 3 - Stable v1.0.0

No target release date yet.

(1.4) Architecture Direction

The next major step is to evolve Mech from a reactive language implementation into a database-backed, embeddable, live, distributed, capability-oriented runtime.

The `v0.2` data specification and `v0.3` program specification remain the foundation. The `v0.4` system specification should define how Mech programs are hosted, permissioned, persisted, updated, distributed, inspected, and recovered.

The guiding architecture is:

```text
Host Application
  -> Embedding API
  -> Runtime Kernel
      -> Mech language engine
      -> Capability kernel
      -> Scheduler / actors / tasks
      -> Live programming system
      -> Database runtime layer
      -> Distributed runtime layer
  -> Database / event log / object store
```

Core principles:

- Code runs with explicit capabilities.
- State changes happen through transactions.
- Long-lived computation is represented as actors, tasks, or state machines.
- Live changes are versioned and migrated.
- Distribution moves messages and capabilities, not raw memory.
- The database records identity, state, authority, and history.

